    "keywords" -> {"logical Pauli operators", "stabilizer formalism"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Tech Note", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "Stabilizer codes are a class of quantum codes with construction based on \
the stabilizer formalism. The idea was put forward by Gottesman (1996, 1997, \
1998). See also Section 6.4 of the Quantum Workbook (2022). Let \
\\[ScriptCapitalS] be the stabilizer of a code space \\[ScriptCapitalV]. \
Suppose that \\[ScriptCapitalV] is corrupted by an error operator E in the \
Pauli group \\[ScriptCapitalP] (n). What would happen to the code space? \
There are three distinctive cases:", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, 
    "title" -> "Stabilizer Codes", "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> 
    "", "windowtitle" -> "Stabilizer Codes", "type" -> "Tech Note", "uri" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/StabilizerCodes"}},
